metadata.name: Disarrangement #112
metadata.description:
This work represents the joy of playing with variables. Oftentimes, the results of my coding are unintended. If there is beauty in the chaos and maybe some structure it is all by chance.  

Fully generative, multiple color combinations, four blending modes, eight backgrounds, scalable. Scaling may lead to shifting and slight differences in the patterns.  
Press 's' to save .png
Coded using p5js: https://p5js.org/

Generative artwork by Dora Vlady,  @lemonvlady on Twitter, 2022.

metadata.name: Missingno #302
metadata.description:
Containment has been breached and Missingno is on the loose. 
This unique beast doesn’t have a fixed shape and its appearance is ever-changing. 
Some call it a bug, very few know what it is truly made of.

Only now with present technology we managed to capture a fraction of its unlimited possible faces. 

Mint for a unique picture of Missingno, yet outdated the very moment it’s taken.


(Open live and click on the image to export)

objkt.name: A creative tunnel that leads to nothing #435

metadata.name: A creative tunnel that leads to nothing #435
metadata.description:
This piece is dedicated to all those forgotten projects that have been left behind, maybe they were just simple ideas that didn't stick, or maybe full blown complex creations, never completed, never released...just stuff on the walls of a tunnel that ends into nothing.

Goodbye.

Time to move on.

#tezosartweek
